      "outcome": "The Wardens pull back from the canal approach, ending their blockade of the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier. The Signal-House Families immediately reclaim full access to their pier, and gondola traffic resumes unimpeded. However, the Wardens' garrison at Tower Bridge Concourse is now at full strength — a formidable defensive position. The bureaucratic envoy is received by the Council, but the hearing is delayed indefinitely as the Council prioritizes its Silent Spire consecration efforts. The Wardens' petition enters the Council's backlog, unlikely to be resolved before high-water season. In the meantime, the Wardens begin quietly recruiting additional guards from the Canal Market District's disaffected merchant class — those who lost business when the Families' subsidized freight undercut traditional trade routes. A small but loyal mercenary contingent begins forming at Tower Bridge.",
